ca.uwo.csd.cs2212.team9

Class LongTermWeather

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uwo.csd.cs2212.team9.LongTermWeather
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ShortTermWeather

    public class LongTermWeather
extends java.lang.Object
    The class retrieves the daily forecast for the next 5 days as a JSON string. The JSON string is parsed and each daily forecast data is stored in a container class and the 5 day data is stored in a vector container. Each individual JSON component have data member associated within the nested class container.
    Author:
    Amha Tsegaye 2212 2015 Team9

    • Constructor Detail

      • LongTermWeather

        public LongTermWeather()
        The default constructor for LongTermWeather class access the API from openweather.org put the JSON file as a string in DataJson data member. If the URL can not be reached it result in IOException. If successfully retrieves the JSON value it calls the helper class fillDataWeatherData method to update the data members in the DataWeatherData container.

      • LongTermWeather

        public LongTermWeather(java.lang.String city)
        An overridden constructor with a string argument that accepts a specific city to get the API from openweather.org and stores the JSON file as a string in DataJson data member. If the URL can not be reached it result in IOException. If successfully retrieves the JSON value it calls the helper class fillDataWeatherData method to update the data members in the DataWeatherData container.
        Parameters:
        city - city name as a string

      • LongTermWeather

        public LongTermWeather(java.lang.String city,
                       java.lang.String country)
        An overridden constructor with a two string argument that accepts a specific city and country to get the API from openweather.org and stores the JSON file as a string in DataJson data member. If the URL can not be reached it result in IOException. If successfully retrieves the JSON value it calls the helper class fillDataWeatherData method to update the data members in the DataWeatherData container.
        Parameters:
        city - city name as a string
        country - country name as a string
